			    <HR color=#000000 SIZE=-1>
			  	I thought that Artifact Cooling Engine gave a 50% reduction to cooling time.  And because of the minuses to detection, it definately belongs in the back of the formation (where the Distortion Blaster ships reside).<br />
<br />
And for those that don't know why the Xesperados would fire first, it's because level 18+ Xesperdo commanders with Psychic Progenitor have full cloaking capability as well as full cloaking detection.  That means that only the Xeloss and Bosalian commanders with Mental Giant have a chance at firing first.<br />
<br />
And as an extra bonus, the rule of thumb is that if you know you will fire first you want a bunch of HBH weapons, and if you know you will fire a whole bunch of times you want high efficiency weapons like Distortion Blaster or Nahodoom Launcher (Energy Systems Specialist + Artifact Crystal + the High Energy Focus device).  Also, keep the high efficiency weapons in the back of your fleet and the missiles at the front.  And DON'T mix weapons on ships, use mixed fleets if you want more than one weapon type on the battlefield.			   <P align=right></P>
			</TD>
